For installatiion of postgresql
- sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib

To check the package details of the postgresql
-apt show postgresql

To check the status of the postgresql
-sudo systemctl status postgresql.service

To set the password of the postgresql
-sudo passwd postgres

To connect to the postgresql
- sudo su -l postgres

To open postgres using command line
-sudo -u postgres psql

To list all the databases avaiable in the postgresql
-SELECT datname FROM pg_database;

To use a particular database
- \c database_name

To shows all tables in the current schema
- \dt

